class Solution:
    def insertIntoBST(self, root: Optional[TreeNode], val: int) -> Optional[TreeNode]:
        if not root:
            return TreeNode(val)

        current = root
        while True:
            if val < current.val:
                if current.left:
                    current = current.left
                else:
                    current.left = TreeNode(val)
                    break
            else:
                if current.right:
                    current = current.right
                else:
                    current.right = TreeNode(val)
                    break

        return root
```

This solution iteratively finds the correct position to insert the new value in the BST. If the current node's value is greater than the new value, it moves to the left child; otherwise, it moves to the right child. When it finds an empty spot (either left or right child is `None`), it inserts the new node there.
